msgid "Composite Roles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/roles/composite.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Any realm or client level role can be turned into a _composite role_.\n"
"A _composite role_ is a role that has one or more additional roles associated with it.\n"
"When a composite role is mapped to the user, the user also gains the roles associated with that composite.  This inheritance\n"
"is recursive so any composite of composites also gets inherited.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/roles/composite.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "To turn a regular role into a composite role, go to the role detail page and flip the `Composite Role` switch on.\n"
msgstr ""

